<TITLE> Bangladesh, UK climate talks start Sept 10 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 8 (bdnews24.com)A UK-Bangladesh climate change conference, titled "Bangladesh: facing the challenge', will be held in London from Sept10. The objective of the conference, to be jointly organised by the governments of the two countries, is to increase international focus on the adverse effect of global warming in Bangladesh. It will address how Bangladesh is adapting to climate change and actions needed to minimalise and combat the consequences. The Bangladesh delegation, to be led by finance and planning adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam, will present a national climate change management strategy at the conference. The other members of the delegation are among others: special assistant to the chief adviser in charge of environment Raja Devashish Roy, secretaries of the ministries of environment and forests, agriculture and the external resources division, Bangladesh high commissioner to the UK Shafi U Ahmed, Chairman of Transparency International Bangladesh Muzaffar Ahmad, chairman of Climate Action Network, South Asia Dr Atiq Rahman, Dr Ainun Nishat of IUCN and president of Bangladesh Environmental Journalists' Forum Quamrul Islam Officials of the UK government and international development agencies will also attend the conference. bdnews2
